author: Matt Shuham
title: Obama Urges Good-Faith Political Participation In Farewell Address
text:
In the final major address of his presidency, President Barack Obama encouraged an enthusiastic crowd in his “adopted hometown” of Chicago to continue engaging in the political process despite what he called "challenges to our democracy."
